parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected deployment of airbags can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities. It can also lead to a loss of vehicle control, especially if the airbags deploy while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The airbags deploy suddenly and without warning
often while the vehicle is in motion
and sometimes without any apparent reason or trigger. The deployment may occur on the passenger side

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Electrical Connection in Seat Belt Clasp
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty electrical connection in the seat belt clasp can prevent the airbags from deploying in the event of a crash, putting the occupants at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light on the dashboard is illuminated
indicating a problem with the airbag system. The locking mechanism of the seat belt clasp may still work
but the electrical connection is faulty
preventing the airbags from deploying in an emergency.
